etymologies: early 18th century: from French, named after Marshal de Plessis-Praslin (1598–1675), the French soldier whose cook invented it

definitions: a smooth, sweet substance made by boiling nuts in sugar and grinding the mixture, used especially as a filling for chocolates
shortDefinitions: smooth, sweet substance made by boiling nuts in sugar and grinding mixture

definitions: a crisp or semicrisp candy typically consisting of butter, brown sugar, and pecans.
shortDefinitions: crisp or semicrisp candy made by similar process
